comments: Bey (DET) initiates contact with Harden (BKN), who has established a legal guarding position in his path.
Johnson (BKN) is already in Grant's (DET) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.

Claxton (BKN) is moving alongside Joseph's (DET) path and maintains a legal guarding position as he defends the drive.

Harris (BKN) faces up with Plumlee (DET), impeding Plumlee from securing the rebound.
Claxton (BKN) is already in McGruder's (DET) path and releases away from the contact.

As he swipes for the ball, Grant (DET) makes some contact with Claxton's (BKN) head after he has secured the ball.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
McGruder (DET) legally contests Harden's (BKN) jump shot attempt.
Harden (BKN) commits a take foul on Plumlee (DET).
Harris (BKN) and McGruder (DET) make incidental leg to leg contact with one another off ball.

Griffin (BKN) clamps and holds Plumlee's (DET) arm, restricting his ability to secure the rebound.
Bey (DET) wraps Griffin (BKN) and restricts his ability to get to the ball.
